    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nHere we translate vim diagnostic to lsp:\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/724d1110b1e4699a34f489e9cdb2d25098746499/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/diagnostic.lua#L164\r\nBut it's doing it incorrectly. It doesn't respect LSP offset_encoding and makes wrong encoding. So, nvim sends wrong position in such case like:\r\n\r\n```go\r\nfunc привет() { // if such code will have diagnostic pointing to 'привет', nvim will send to lsp position as end=17 instead of end=11\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe it's a bug cause at other places offset_encoding is handling correctly, like here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/724d1110b1e4699a34f489e9cdb2d25098746499/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua#L902\r\n\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0",
    "closed_at": "2024-08-01T14:01:16Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "As a workaround, I made such thing, with the help of `vim.lsp.util.character_offset`:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal function get_diagnostic_at_cursor()\r\n  local cur_buf = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\r\n  local line, col = unpack(vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0))\r\n  local entrys = vim.diagnostic.get(cur_buf, { lnum = line - 1 })\r\n  local res = {}\r\n  for _, v in pairs(entrys) do\r\n    if v.col <= col and v.end_col >= col then\r\n      table.insert(res, {\r\n        code = v.code,\r\n        message = v.message,\r\n        range = {\r\n          ['start'] = {\r\n            character = vim.lsp.util.character_offset(cur_buf, v.lnum, v.col, 'utf-16'),\r\n            line = v.lnum,\r\n          },\r\n          ['end'] = {\r\n            character = vim.lsp.util.character_offset(cur_buf, v.end_lnum, v.end_col, 'utf-16'),\r\n            line = v.end_lnum,\r\n          },\r\n        },\r\n        severity = v.severity,\r\n        source = v.source or nil,\r\n      })\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\n  return res\r\nend\r\n-- Execute a code action, usually your cursor needs to be on top of an error\r\n-- or a suggestion from your LSP for this to activate.\r\nmap('<leader>ca', function()\r\n  vim.lsp.buf.code_action {\r\n    context = {\r\n      diagnostics = get_diagnostic_at_cursor(),\r\n    },\r\n  }\r\nend, '[C]ode [A]ction')\r\n\r\n```",
